570402205.text: "ERK (1/2) phosphorylation induced by stimulation of either 5-HT (2B) or 5-HT (2C) receptors was mediated by epidermal growth factor (EGF) receptor transactivation (Peng et al., this issue), shown by the inhibitory effect of AG1478, an inhibitor of the EGF receptor tyrosine kinase, and GM6001, an inhibitor of Zn dependent metalloproteinases, and thus of 5-HT (2B) receptor mediated EGF receptor agonist release."
